3D Printing & Modeling

I have been teaching myself the usage and concepts needed for 3d Printing over the last couple years, having printed everything from Architectural models to a car spoiler and composite molds.

Modeled is my Ender 3 Pro which is somehow still running along with a couple of objects I have printed, including 2 carbon fibre parts which used 3d printed molds.

To accompany my 3D printing, I have also been teaching myself how to use CAD software namely freeCAD, along with the slicing software needed to translate this into a print file. During my time at Scion I was introduced to 3D gaussians, which is whats being used to display my model. These 3d Models can be used to create printable objects which I did at Scion when a 3d scanner was able to quite get the details on a small object.
